# teardown()

### 

​

`function` `teardown`
    
    
    teardown(exit_code: 'int | None' = None) → None
    

Waits for W&B to finish and frees resources. Completes any runs that were not explicitly finished using `run.finish()` and waits for all data to be uploaded. It is recommended to call this at the end of a session that used `wandb.setup()`. It is invoked automatically in an `atexit` hook, but this is not reliable in certain setups such as when using Python’s `multiprocessing` module.

